Volunteer, Sponsor or Donate
The Frog Leg Festival has come a long way since the first 400 dinners sold in 1990.  The success of this annual event is due to a very dedicated and hard working group of volunteers who come out every year to help serve up these frog leg dinners to thousands of people.  Over the years, this group of people has helped
raise over $1,000,000
that has been contributed back to the City Of Fellsmere for the recreational needs of the children and to the dozens of volunteer groups and organizations who come out to help put on the festival.
We are always looking for volunteers to help with the organization and execution of the Frog Leg Festival.  If you are interested in volunteering your time and talents please fill out the form below and our Volunteer Coordinator will contact you.
Volunteer opportunities include, but are not limited to: Ticket Sales, Beverage Sales, Food Preparation and Kitchen Duties, Volunteer Coordination, Site Management and Entertainment Support.
Let us know how you'd like to get in on the gig that's been supporting Fellsmere's youth for 33 years!
